[0.100, "o", "\u001b[H\n \u001b[1;38;2;255;68;68mgodshell❯ \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;204;204;204mMain finding: this snapshot looks user-driven and dev-heavy, not obviously compromised. Evidence: summary shows\u001b[m     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mmultiple interactive shells, kitty, asciinema, Chrome/Firefox, and two live ./godshell instances under zsh parents (PIDs\u001b[m      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m250968, 260796), both reading /home/raul/.config/godshell/config.json and making only a few connections.\u001b[0m                      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mMost notable process is PID 4402, antigravity language_server_linux_x64, because it is hot and noisy. Evidence: summary\u001b[m       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mshows 34.38% CPU, 933516 KB RAM, 52394 connections, dominated by 1.1.1.1:853 and HTTPS, plus repeated opens of\u001b[m                \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m/home/raul/Desktop/projects/godshell/godshelldemo.cast.\u001b[0m                                                                       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mLineage suggests current activity is local terminal recording/testing. Evidence: summary shows zsh/asciinema chains and live\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mgodshell under /usr/bin/zsh; also recently exited git, starship, fzf, nproc processes are consistent with shell prompt/repo\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mwork.\u001b[0m                                                                                                                         \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mNetwork pattern is broad but mostly resolver-heavy rather than clear C2. Evidence: many unrelated processes show 1.1.1.1:853\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mincluding systemd-resolved PID 430, NetworkManager PID 928, Firefox PID 53566, Chrome/Electron components, and godshell;\u001b[m      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mthat points to shared DoT/DNS behavior in the environment, not one rogue beacon by itself.\u001b[0m                                    \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mGhost activity is benign-looking shell churn. Evidence: recently_exited is mostly short-lived\u001b[m                                 \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mgit/starship/zsh/hyprctl/cliphist/systemd-userwork with tiny lifespans and no standout outbound pattern.\u001b[0m                      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mIf you want, next I can drill into 1) the Antigravity/Electron tree, 2) the live godshell processes, or 3) shell history for\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204muser raul before you send snapshot two.\u001b[0m                                                                                       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136myou❯ \u001b[0mwhat new processes spawned on this new snapshot?                                                                         \u001b[K\r\n   \u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;255;255;255;48;2;204;34;0m◈ summary\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;204;34;0m \u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;153;153;153m11 groups · 49 processes · 38 exited · \u001b[1;38;2;255;136;102mtop: /usr/lib/antigravit… 33.5%\u001b[0m\u001b[0m                                         \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[1;38;2;255;68;68mgodshell❯ \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;204;204;204mNo new active processes spawned between the two snapshots. Evidence: every active PID in the 13:17:47 snapshot was\u001b[m  \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204malready present in the 13:17:11 snapshot.\u001b[0m                                                                                     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                      "]
